<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-836] regression with surefire 2.12 plugin and SecurityManager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-836</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are running all our tests using a special security manager that restricts IO in tests. There is a regression when running these tests with the 2.12 plugin compared to the 2.11 plugin:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) git clone git@github.com:NessComputing/components-ness-pg.git&lt;br/&gt;
2) mvn clean compile test-compile&lt;br/&gt;
3) Run the tests with the 2.11 plugin: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mvn -Dtest=TestPostgresUtils org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-surefire-plugin:2.11:test&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INFO&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Scanning for projects...&lt;br/&gt;
