                            <comment id="14455368" author="krosenvold" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2012 09:45:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test project seems to require a database ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455288" author="henning" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2012 10:42:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No, the TestPostgresUtils does not. That is why you should run it with -Dtest=TestPostgresUtils&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you do have a local postgres that allows connection as postgres user without a password, then all tests can be run. The result is the same, though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
